<title type="html"><![CDATA[2/13 (Thu.) Valentine's Day / Gaming Time (Host: Nora)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=362&amp;p=379#p379"><![CDATA[
<span style="color: #FF0000">***** Removal Notice *****<br />We'd like to inform you that the Thursday gathering of Royal English Club is relocated to new venue.<br />New address: Ikari Coffee 怡客咖啡, 台北市中正區衡陽路116號</span><br /><br /><br />Session 1:<br />It’s Valentine’s day tomorrow. What are you going to celebrate it?Let's check out these videos below.<br /><br />1-1 The difference between healthy and unhealthy love | Katie Hood<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ON4iy8hq2hM&amp;feature=emb_logo">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ON4iy8h ... e=emb_logo</a><!-- m --><br /><br />We have three main goals: give all of us a language for talking about a subject that’s quite awkward and uncomfortable to discuss; empower a whole front line, namely friends, to help; and, in the process, improve all of our ability to love better.<br /><br />1-2 Valentines Day Gone Wrong<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/44036">https://tw.voicetube.com/videos/44036</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Questions.<br />What do you think which unhealthy sign that people frequently miss?<br />What do you do to keep your relationship(friends, romantic partner or family) stronger and longer?<br />How do you teach your children to love?<br />What do you think about Valentine's day?<br /><br />Extra Video 1-3 The Quints Help Make Mother's Day Breakfast<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ckMSM7VajBE">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ckMSM7VajBE</a><!-- m --><br />Hehe, the third video is not about Valentine’s day, but it’s adorable and also a way to celebrate for Valentine’s day.<br /><br />-------------------------------------------------------------------------<br /><br />Session 2: Gaming time!<br />We will play some group games like mafia game. Come here and  with pleasant mood.<br /><br /><br /><br />===================================================<br /><br />Agenda<br />7:00 pm - 7:20 pm Free talk<br />7:20 pm - 7:50 pm First topic discussion<br />7:50 pm - 8:20 pm Presentation (At least two members of each table are invited)<br />8:20 pm - 8:30 pm Break time &amp; Group picture<br />8:30 pm - 9:20 pm Session 2<br />9:20 pm - 9:30 pm Feedback &amp; Guest introduction<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=25437">Michael</a> — Sun Feb 09, 2020 3:36 pm</p><hr />
